    <question>
        <prompt>What characterized the relationship between Theodore Roosevelt and William Howard Taft?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">They were always enemies</option>
            <option letter="b">They went from friends to political rivals</option>
            <option letter="c">They remained close allies</option>
            <option letter="d">They never interacted</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Roosevelt and Taft were close friends until political differences, especially over progressive reforms, led to their famous split and the creation of Roosevelt's Bull Moose Party.</explanation>
